Key Match Events: Emilio Nsue scored the winning goal in the 64th minute for Equatorial Guinea against Namibia.
Teenage striker Chifundo Mphasi scored the winning goal in the 78th minute for Malawi against Liberia.
Pre-Game Insights: Liberia were denied a dream start to the 2026 World Cup qualifiers as they suffered a 1-0 defeat at the hands of Malawi.
Equatorial Guinea picked up a 1-0 victory over Namibia at the Nuevo Estadio de Malabo.
Liberia have now lost five games on the bounce and are without a win in their last eight across all competitions.
Equatorial Guinea have won one of their five competitive games in 2023.
